      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "One of the most persistent advo-\nGates of the proposed union passen-\nger station Is the North Coast rail-\nway. The North Coast seems to\nthink, however, that unless the city\ncouncil reduces the price of the city\nhall property $4,000 there is no\nshow for the union depot project\ngoing through.\n\n\nHence the chief counsel for the\nroad, l.. r. Hamblen. former attor-\nney for the city. has been calling\ncouncilmen to his office, one by\none, and interviewing them on their\nfeeling toward cutting the price\nplaced on the city hall property\nfrom $500 to S275,000, The first\nfigure was agreed upon by the city\ncouncil after careful deliberation"
    }
